Which of the below is NOT a characteristic of proactive problem management ?
Select the best answer.

A.
Data mining and deep dives should be performed to identify further opportunities.
B.
Service reviews and performance reporting (trending analysis) are key inputs to proactively identifying opportunities.
C.
Problem records are created as a direct result of incidents.
D.
Problem records may be opened by service, application/product owners, and/or problem managers as they identify weaknesses in applications and/or the infrastructure, and develop proposals to eliminate those weaknesses.
